Frequently Asked Questions
Feel free to browse the most commonly asked customer questions.  If you don't find what you need, please
contact us
or reach out to your local agent.

question.en-US: I was just in an automobile accident with another driver.  What should I do?

content.value: It is important to contact the police if you feel you are not responsible for the accident or if injuries have occurred.  A police officer can document accident details that may become important later.

People often forget details of an accident in short period of time.  Take a moment to jot down the details.  Consider the direction travelled, speed, and lane for each vehicle.  How far was the other vehicle from you when you saw it?
Get names and contact information from all witnesses, injured persons and all occupants of the vehicles.  It is helpful to get insurance information from the other driver.
Do not admit fault.
Your adjuster will provide you with additional information concerning the claims process.  You will be contacted within 2 business days after the loss as been reported.

question.en-US: Do I need to use a body shop associated with NCFB?

content.value: No
, we work with reputable shops across the state.  We do not require the use of specific shops.

question.en-US: Are deductibles waived on glass replacement?

content.value: No

, your deductible is not waived on a glass replacement claim.  In North Carolina, glass replacement falls under your comprehensive coverage.  If you carry a deductible on your comprehensive coverage, your deductible will apply.

question.en-US: Does NC Farm Bureau waive the comprehensive deductible for chip repair?

content.value: Yes
, if the repair fails or you decide later to have the windshield replaced, you will be responsible for your deductible at the time of the replacement.

question.en-US: Do I have Towing and Labor Coverage?

content.value: Towing and Labor coverage is sold as an additional endorsement (NC0304) under your personal auto policy / business auto policy.  You can review your coverage located on your declaration page.

question.en-US: If my policy shows that I have unlimited towing does that mean I can have my vehicle towed anywhere?

content.value: No
, the policy states that "we will pay towing and labor costs incurred…for towing to the nearest place where necessary repairs can be made."

question.en-US: Can I remove a tree from my damaged structure without prior approval from an agent or claims adjuster?

content.value: Yes

, your policy will cover to remove the tree from a damaged covered structure.  Your policy will only pay the reasonable cost to remove the tree off the structure and place it onto the ground.  Some policies give an aggregate allowance to remove the tree off the insured premises.  We do not pay for the removal of a tree that is leaning toward a structure and not touching it.

question.en-US: Can I complete temporary repairs without approval from a claims adjuster?

content.value: Yes

, your policy actually requires that you take all necessary steps to protect your property from further damage.  You should make sure you get detailed receipts for these temporary repairs and present them to your claims adjuster.

seoDescription.en-US: My mission as a Farm Bureau agent is to structure an insurance program to meet the needs, and budget, of each individual. I want to make sure each persons standard of living is protected in the event of a car accident, house fire, death in the family, etc. I am dedicated to providing long-term personal and educated service to the clients I represent. With the utmost ethical standards and integrity, my success is measured by more than just selling a product; it's measured by the relationships I build.
